and the one before.

90
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:33,283
I know you're smart,
and I'm proud of you.

91
00:09:33,366 --> 00:09:37,912
I want you to get out into the fresh air
and make some friends.

92
00:09:37,996 --> 00:09:41,458
Run around,
scrape your knees, get dirty.

93
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:43,460
Climb trees, hop fences.

94
00:09:43,543 --> 00:09:46,796
Get into trouble,
for crying out loud.

95
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:49,883
Not too much, but some.
You have my permission.

96
00:09:50,008 --> 00:09:53,470
How many mothers do you know who
say something like that to their sons?

97
00:09:53,553 --> 00:09:56,264
Well, none mothers, I guess.

98
00:09:56,348 --> 00:10:01,019
Honey, I want you to make
some friends this summer. Lots of them.

99
00:10:02,145 --> 00:10:04,105
Yeah, I know.

100
00:10:04,189 --> 00:10:06,107
But I'm not good
at anything, Mom.

101
00:10:06,191 --> 00:10:08,109
Face it,
I'm just an egghead.

102
00:10:08,193 --> 00:10:12,656
Honey, you'll always be just an egghead
